(81, 1, 1, '2021-06-18 00:00:00', 'https://www.namibian.com.na/102608/read/From-The-Twittersphere', 'Entertainment ', 'From The Twittersphere', 'THE struggle is real. Behavioural patterns are important. And the choices we make have consequences, whether they''re for the common good or self-indulgent. Covid is no respecter of people. It''s an ever-present danger. Let''s act accordingly… For now, pithy perspectives from Twitter TLs…@OtherShirley: Imagine calling a 45-year-old man “babe”. Otamu lundukitha aakulupe nayi, muhn@Josy_Ndili: Etseeee, imagine if we were in a Zombie Apocalypse and Usain Bolt turned into the Head Zombie.... Yesses, man@QuecianaWalton: People who don''t wear their seatbelt irritate me like you just wanna fly out the window, huh?@Bottleshaped_na: People are always asking what problems we have at our age. Bra, my phone shuts down at 79%.@_FNNS__: Me and squandering money, you''d think we''re lovers...@m_a_g_g_z: I am trying to choose peace but the homophobes and anti-vaxxers are testing your girl this week@carolina75011: Today''s bane – people who want to control everything but not take actual responsibility.@lovinbryn: Students disrespecting teachers will never be funny to meCovid Caution@Gazza467_: Good morning my people, please take extra caution. People are dying and Covid is real… I still have hope that we can beat this thing but it will take a nation to work in harmony. Let''s forget our differences for a while and fight the common enemy as one Namibia, one Nation@MelvinAngula: If you are worried about the vaccine, then please also stay home and don''t be part of the problem. Medical staff are asking you to vaccinate… If you don''t want to, at least stay home so that you don''t fill up the hospitals when you''re infected and make it their burden.@GreezyThaDon: Don''t take any interest nor mack on me if you''re not vaccinated. Thank you, good night@anne_hambuda: Thankful that my mom and dad exercise and eat right and don''t believe in WhatsA