(118, 2, 2, '2021-06-19 00:00:00', 'https://postcourier.com.pg/wnb-government-partners-with-chamber-of-commerce/', 'National News', ' WNB government partners with Chamber of Commerce ', '   By NICOLE JOANNES The West New Britain Provincial Government is partnering with the Chamber of Commerce and Industry for the use of PSIP funds allocated to Kimbe police. They have entered a memorandum of agreement for the Chamber of Commerce to disburse the funds to service providers upon submissions presented by the police. The agreement provides the guidelines for the use of the K500,000 presented to chamber by the regional Member Sasindran Muthuvel. This agreement was signed by Provincial Administrator Williamson Hosea, President of the Chamber of Commerce and Industry Ian O’Hanlon and provincial police commander Januarius Vosivai. The focus areas for the funding include the maintenance of the ten new vehicles and firearms, information call centre setup, community policing and other operational areas like CID, intelligence, VHF radios and infrastructures among others. Mr Muthuvel said this will save police time to have access to the money instead of the long government process. He thanked the Chamber of Commerce for the partnership arrangement which has also gone down well with the police. Mr Muthuvel said this arrangement came about following the visit of Lands Minister and Member for Lae John Rosso last year. Mr Rosso had an audience with chamber, and they had agreed for this move to cut down on time and to improve the response time of the police that is aimed at improving law and order. Meanwhile the acting assistant commissioner of police for NGI Paul Kamuai has thanked the provincial government and the Chamber of Commerce for this partnership arrangement. He also thanked the MP for the funding assistance and assured that the money will be used for the intended purposes to improve law and order in the province. Mr Kamuai said the expenditure on the use of the funding will be provided by PPC Vosivai.   ', NULL, NULL),
