(124, 2, 2, '2021-06-19 00:00:00', 'https://postcourier.com.pg/by-election-quality-checks-put-on-hold/', 'Top Stories', ' By-election quality checks put on hold ', '   BY THIERRY LEPANI Quality checks of the first preference votes counted at the various wards continues to drag on through the week after officials and scrutineers finally got their brief yesterday at the Sir John Guise stadium by officials. The quality checks were supposed to start at 2pm yesterday, however difficulties with ensuring counting officials were identified resulted in police going through the task of calling names of officials and checking identification. Shortly after, scrutineers on site refused to participate after news of a purported petition by a number of candidates outlining grievances was to be presented to the Returning Officer. After some time, the scrutineers came to a compromise and one-by-one entered the premises under the supervision of police to get briefed on the quality checks. Electoral officials then gathered the counting officials and scrutineers in the counting centre and gave them a rundown of the quality checks process. An official explained that the container with the ward 11 ballot boxes would be the first to undergo quality checks. The official said after the quality checks are completed, the progressive scores will be confirmed before heading to elimination. Officials were made aware that the criteria for an invalid ballot must be double checked on all ballots – ensuring the correct name of the candidate for the appropriate box is indicated. Quality checks for the different wards are set to progress today; however, almost certain it will be marred with delays and confusion.   ', NULL, NULL),
