(144, 2, 2, '2021-06-19 00:00:00', 'https://postcourier.com.pg/solomon-cup-attracts-50-teams-in-bialla/', 'Sports', ' Solomon Cup attracts 50 teams in Bialla ', '   Local resident in Bialla town West New Britain Andrew Solomon has pledged K50,000 for Solomon Cup which will run for 20 weeks as soccer (male teams – 18 & female teams – 12) and volleyball (eight male teams and 12 female teams) competition. Solomon said at this time when law and order issues are at its highest peak in West New Britain, he pledged his support to the youths (boys and girls) in Bialla town with these competitions. He said Bialla has created history and has potential to produce super stars like Marcus Bai in rugby league. He said he will officiate at another competition around July in Kabaiya LSS, Noau village, Lolobau Island, Silanga, Marapu and Ubai village in Bialla LLG with a similar financial support before moving into Mosa LLG, Hoskins LLG, Kimbe Urban LLG, Talasea LLG and Bali Witu LLG. Rugby league will soon start in all local level governments too. He met with Sports Minister Wesley Raminai last week to deliver an official invitation to officiate at the Solomon Cup grand finals in October and is expected to be accompanied by PNG Football Association president, PNG Volleyball Association president, PNGRFL chairman and PNG Sports Federation chief executive officer. There will also be a district games that will see sides selected from each LLG to compete for K200,000 in various sports. He said his priority games are rugby league, soccer, volleyball and basketball and developing raw talent onto professionals. He said his main focus is to support Team West New Britain prepare for PNG Games in Mendi, Southern Highlands Province that is expected to be held in November this year.     ', NULL, NULL),
