(155, 2, 2, '2021-06-19 00:00:00', 'https://postcourier.com.pg/empower-women/', 'National News', ' ‘Empower women’ ', '   BY PATRICK TOM WOMEN play important role in the community and they deserve to be supported in any way possible to empower them. Australia High Commissioner to Papua New Guinea Jon Philp says the roles women play in their respective families and communities entitle them to be given a voice to stand up and participate in the community. Mr Philp told the women group during the financial literacy 16th graduation that they (women) are important and should be given the power of choice to participate in any decision making and be part of the community. “Women are a manager of the family, and house thus it’s important that we give every woman in our society the opportunity to participate,” he said. “For the children to be better educated it comes back to how educated the mothers are and this helps empower the family, community and society as whole.”
He said PNG needs women leaders and it is time we give equal opportunity to women to take the country forward. NCDC Women Commissioner Elice Siki urges the women to take every opportunity in whatever things they are venturing in to empower their family, clan and society. She said on behalf of all the women, she acknowledges the presence of the Australian High Commissioner Jon Philp for attending their graduation and presenting them the certificates. “Women are vital part of community development and I represent all the women in the city and this gives me great pleasure to see what these women are undergoing, the basic financial literacy training,”   ', NULL, NULL),
