(161, 2, 2, '2021-06-19 00:00:00', 'https://postcourier.com.pg/empower-women/', 'National News', ' ‘Empower women’ ', '   BY PATRICK TOM WOMEN play important role in the community and they deserve to be supported in any way possible to empower them. Australia High Commissioner to Papua New Guinea Jon Philp says the roles women play in their respective families and communities entitle them to be given a voice to stand up and participate in the community. Mr Philp told the women group during the financial literacy 16th graduation that they (women) are important and should be given the power of choice to participate in any decision making and be part of the community. “Women are a manager of the family, and house thus it’s important that we give every woman in our society the opportunity to participate,” he said. “For the children to be better educated it comes back to how educated the mothers are and this helps empower the family, community and society as whole.”
